obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47577)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Inter-State Corporations Act, 1957.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257&sectionId=47577&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47578)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1960, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257&sectionId=47578&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, "inter-State corporation" means any body corporate constituted under any`
  line `of the Acts specified in the Schedule and functioning in two or more States by virtue of section 109 of the`
  line `States Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956),`
  line ^1
  line `[or of any other enactment relating to reorganisation of`
  line States.]
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47579)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of State Governments to frame schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257&sectionId=47579&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Government of a State in`
  line `any part of which an inter-State corporation is functioning that the inter-State corporation should be`
  line `reconstituted and reorganised as one or more inter-State corporations or that it should be dissolved, the`
  line `State Government may frame a scheme for such reconstitution and reorganisation or such dissolution, as`
  line `the case may be, including proposals regarding the transfer of the assets, rights and liabilities of the`
  line `inter-State corporation to any other corporations or State Governments and the transfer or re-employment`
  line `of employees of the inter-State corporation and forward the scheme to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47580)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Reorganisation of certain inter-State corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257&sectionId=47580&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of a scheme forwarded to it`
  line `under section 3, the Central Government may, after consulting the State Governments concerned, approve`
  line `the scheme with or without modifications and give effect to the scheme so approved by making such`
  line `order as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) An order made under sub-section (1) may provide for all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the dissolution of the inter-State corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) the reconstitution and reorganisation in any manner whatsoever of the inter-State corporation`
  line `including the constitution, where necessary, of new corporations;`
  line
  line `(c) the area in respect of which the reconstituted corporation or new corporation shall function`
  line `and operate;`
  line
  line `(d) the transfer, in whole or in part, of the assets, rights and liabilities of the inter-State`
  line `corporation (including the rights and liabilities under any contract made by it) to any other`
  line `corporations or State Governments and the terms and conditions of such transfer;`
  line
  line `(e) the substitution of any such transferee for the inter-State corporation, or the addition of any`
  line `such transferee, as a party to any legal proceeding to which the inter-State corporation is a party; and`
  line `the transfer of any proceedings pending before the inter-State corporation to any such transferee;`
  line
  line `(f) the transfer or re-employment of any employees of the inter-State corporation to, or by, any`
  line `such transferee and subject to the provisions of section 111 of the States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956 (37 of 1956),`
  line ^1
  line `[or of any other enactment relating to reorganisation of States] the terms and`
  line `conditions of service applicable to such employees after such transfer or re-employment;`
  line
  line `(g) the adaptations or modifications of the Act under which the inter-State corporation was`
  line `constituted, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be necessary or expedient to give effect`
  line `to the approved scheme;`
  line
  line `(h) such incidental, consequential and supplementary matters as may be necessary to give effect`
  line `to the approved scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an order is made under this section transferring the assets, rights and liabilities of any`
  line `inter-State corporation, then, by virtue of that order, such assets, rights and liabilities of the inter-State`
  line `corporation shall vest in, and be the assets, rights and liabilities of, the transferee.`
  line
  line `(4) Every order made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette and the Act under`
  line `which the inter-State corporation was constituted shall have effect subject to the provisions of the order`
  line `and the adaptations and modifications made thereby until altered, repealed or amended by the competent`
  line `Legislature of a State.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(5) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1960, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47581)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Central Government to add to the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1960, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257&sectionId=47581&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00034_195738_1517807322257
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in the Schedule any Act under which a body corporate`
  line `constituted for a State is functioning in two or more States by virtue of section 109 of the States`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956),`
  line ^1
  line `[or of any other enactment relating to reorganisation of States]`
  line `and on the issue of such notification, the Schedule shall be deemed to be amended by the inclusion of the`
  line `said Act therein.`
